# CODEOWNERS - Require review for sensitive files
#
# This file defines code ownership for security-critical files and directories.
# Any PR that modifies these files will automatically require approval from the
# specified owners before merging.
#
# Reference: core/security/security-principles.md
# Related: GitHub issue #7 - Service account protection controls

# GitHub Actions workflows - require review for security
# These workflows use the FIREBASE_SERVICE_ACCOUNT with custom IAM permissions
# for Firebase Authentication domain management
/.github/workflows/ @tdeknecht

# GitHub Actions scripts - require review for security
# Any automation scripts should be reviewed to prevent service account misuse
/.github/scripts/ @tdeknecht

# GitHub Actions setup documentation - require review for security
# This file contains service account setup and security best practices
/.github/GITHUB_ACTIONS_SETUP.md @tdeknecht

# Firestore security rules - require review for security
# Database security rules protect user data and must be carefully reviewed
/firestore.rules @tdeknecht

# Firebase configuration - require review for security
# Main Firebase configuration file that affects deployment and security settings
/firebase.json @tdeknecht

# Environment configuration template - require review for security
# Template files that define environment variables and secrets structure
/.env.example @tdeknecht
